purpose: Sustainable fashion for men, women, and children.
description: It was very clean looking with limited information, pictures, and colours. This made it easy to scan quickly and take in most things that were on the page (at least in general). There was a men's, women's, and children's section all of which were linked in the biggest bottom part of the page. The logo was in the top left corner and across the top of the page there seemed to be a menu of sorts.

I tried to look more at the main body of the page and so didn't take in the top (including the name and logo). The main body featured a large picture of what I think were 2 children, or 1 child and 1 adult hugging. I think they were wearing sunglasses and I think my first instinct was that this was a travel website until I looked the categories below the big picture which included glasses and contacts - then I got really confused and then my time was up.

The page had a big tiger in the middle. Again, there was a menu across the top, with at the bottom of the page various options for direct categories - the first of which was clothing. The page was primarily in blue and red and featured pictures of mountains (I think) indicating the outdoorsiness of the brand and its products.

The page had the logo in the top left followed by a menu across the top of the page. On the left of the page was a map with the weather depicted with standard weather symbols - quite a few suns! On the right were links to subpages as well as temperature (I think) predictions for the rest of the week.
